frameDefinitions: An Importer receives Goods from an Exporting_area, across a boundary or border to a different area, the Importing_area.
A Customer requests an Entity from a Supplier.

The words in this frame describe situations in which the Perpetrator secretly takes Goods into or out of a country or other area which are prohibited by law or on which one has not paid the required duty.
An Agent begins preventing a Captive from moving despite a tendency or desire on the part of the Captive to do so.
The words in this frame describe situations in which a Perpetrator carries off and holds the Victim against his or her will by force. ''
The Authorities hold a Suspect under suspicion of having committed a crime (Charges).
frameExamples: The U.S. <t>imported</t> some wheat in the period, although it exported about ten times as much.
I <t>ordered</t> a black scarf from J. Crew a week ago.
Authorities recently <t>captured</t> several suspects who were hiding in a remote mountain area.
Two men <t>kidnapped</t> a Millwall soccer club employee, police said last night.
The police <t>held</t> Mr. Smith in the slammer on charges of killing his lawyer.
listRoleDefinitions: The conscious entity, generally a person, that brings the <fen>Goods</fen> into the <fen>Importing_area</fen>.
The items of value whose location is changing.
The role <fen>Importing_area</fen> is the place that the <fen>Goods</fen> end up as a result of motion.
The place where the <fen>Goods</fen> are initially, before the being moved.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Importer</fen> moves the <fen>Goods</fen>.
The <fen>Customer</fen> is the person or business ordering the <fen>Entity</fen> from the <fen>Supplier</fen>.
The object ordered by the <fen>Customer</fen>.
The person or organization from whom the <fen>Customer</fen> orders the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> at which the <fen>Customer</fen> requested the <fen>Entity</fen>.
This is the person (or other agent) that illegally takes the goods into or out of a country.
The role Goods is anything (including labor, time, or legal rights) that can be illegally taken into our out of a country.
The source is the location the goods occupy initially before change of location.
The path refers to (a part of the) ground the Goods travel over or to a landmark the Goods travel by.
Goal is the location the Goods end up in.

Where the event takes place.

When the event occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the event occurs.

The <fen>Victim</fen> is the person who is carried off and held against his/her will.

Where the kidnapping takes place.
